      <lg type="edition">
<l>pulippāṟ paṭṭa vāmāṉ kuḻavikkuc</l>
<l>ciṉaṅkaḻi mūtāk kaṉṟumaṭut tūṭṭum</l>
<l>kā.....................................................k</l>
<l>kuḷḷiyatu curakku mōmpā vīkai</l>
<l>veḷvē lāva  māyi ṉoḷvāṭ</l>
<l>kaṟaiyaṭi yāṉaik kalla</l>
<l>tuṟaikaḻip paṟiyā vēlō ṉūrē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>Where the old cow whose temperament has calmed down feeds [its] calf</l>
<l>[and also] gives [milk] to the calf of the wild cow that fell a share to the tiger,</l>
<l>……………………………………</l>
<l>the village of the one with a spear who never removes from [its] sheath,</l>
<l>except for the elephant with mortar feet,</l>
<l>[his] bright sword, if there is a war of victorious spears,</l>
<l>of unguarded generosity who showers what[ever] is thought of…</l>
</lg>
